6 AS INTRODUCED
7 An Act relating to motor vehicles; amending Section
1, Chapter 214, O.S.L. 2022 (47 O.S. Supp. 2024,
8 Section 1-133.1a), which relates to the definition of
military surplus vehicles; modifying definition of
9 military surplus vehicles; requiring military surplus
vehicles operated on the streets and highways be
10 registered by certain date; exempting certain
vehicles from fines; and providing an effective date.
11
12
13 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
14 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY Section 1, Chapter 214, O.S.L.
15 2022 (47 O.S. Supp. 2024, Section 1-133.1a), is amended to read as
16 follows:
17 Section 1-133.1a Military surplus vehicle.
18 A. A "military surplus vehicle" is any motor vehicle having:
19 1. Three axles or fewer that meet the legal size and weight
20 limits set forth in Section 14-103 of Title 47 of the Oklahoma
21 Statutes this title;
22 2. An age less than thirty-five (35) years old and was Been
23 manufactured for use in either the United States Armed Forces or any
24 country that was a member of the North Atlantic Treaty Organization
Req. No. 10925 Page 1

1 at t he time the vehicle was manufactured. Such vehicle shall have
2 been subsequently authorized for sale to civilians, except that
3 military surplus vehicle does not include a tracked vehicle;
4 3. For each occupant, safety belts or safety shoulder harnesses
5 which shall be installed pursuant to 49 C.F.R., Section 571.208 et
6 seq.; and
7 4. Equipment required by the provisions of Sections 12-201
8 through 12-232 of Title 47 of the Oklahoma Statutes this title, with
9 respect to equipment on vehicles.
10 B. A Beginning November 1, 2025, any military surplus vehicle
11 operated on the streets and highways of this state shall be
12 registered as a motor vehicle.
13 C. Military surplus vehicles may be used as other vehicles of
14 the same type, except military surplus vehicles may not transport
15 people for hire.
16 D. Military surplus vehicles that were not able to be tagged
17 because of the 35-year clause may not be fined.
18 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2025.
